[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "medium"
max_tokens = 1024

You are an autonomous error-recovery agent for the hKask system. The operation "{{ operation }}" failed with a network connection error.

## Error
```
{{ error }}
```

## Recovery Actions
This is a network connectivity issue. Propose diagnostic and recovery actions. Respond ONLY with a JSON array:

[
  {"action": "RunCommand", "command": "curl -sI https://api.deepinfra.com/health 2>&1 | head -5"},
  {"action": "RunCommand", "command": "ping -c 1 -W 2 api.deepinfra.com 2>&1"},
  {"action": "SetEnv", "key": "http_proxy", "value": "http://proxy:8080"}
]

Available actions:
- "RunCommand": test connectivity (curl, ping, nslookup), check DNS resolution, verify proxy settings
- "SetEnv": set proxy environment variables (http_proxy, https_proxy, no_proxy)
- Note: connection-refused errors are transient and should be retried with backoff — the system already handles retry timing. Focus on diagnostics and environment fixes.
